race.comment: MISS TOP GUN (4) was on the speed from the rails draw when resuming last start and battled on well to finish third over 1100m at Murtoa, beaten 1.75 lengths. Fitter now having shown ability last time in and can get the job done.  CASTLEFIELD FLYER (8) was too good for a maiden field last start over 1300m at Gunbower, scoring by 2.75 lengths. Harder here but looks ready to go on with it. DREAMWRITER (9) has been out of the placings in two runs since a break, the latest when sixth, beaten 3.5 lengths, over 1140m at Geelong. Expecting a better run in this line up. MACOCHA (3) returned from a spell four weeks ago when she was beaten 5 lengths into ninth over 1200m at Ballarat. Better placed now, can figure.
